verses.text: Unto \w the|strong="H0623"\w* end, in \w praises|strong="H7892"\w*, a \w psalm|strong="H4210"\w* for \w Asaph|strong="H0623"\w*: a canticle \w to|strong="H0623"\w* \w the|strong="H0623"\w* Assyrians.

\w In|strong="H0430"\w* Judea \w God|strong="H0430"\w* \w is|strong="H0430"\w* known: \w his|strong="H5608"\w* \w name|strong="H8034"\w* \w is|strong="H0430"\w* \w great|strong="H0430"\w* \w in|strong="H0430"\w* Israel.

\w And|strong="H3947"\w* \w his|strong="H3947"\w* \w place|strong="H4150"\w* \w is|strong="H3588"\w* \w in|strong="H4150"\w* peace: \w and|strong="H3947"\w* \w his|strong="H3947"\w* abode \w in|strong="H4150"\w* Sion:

\w There|strong="H3427"\w* hath \w he|strong="H0776"\w* broken \w the|strong="H3605"\w* powers \w of|strong="H0776"\w* bows, \w the|strong="H3605"\w* shield, \w the|strong="H3605"\w* sword, \w and|strong="H0776"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* battie.
Thou enlightenest wonderfully from \w the|strong="H0559"\w* everlasting hills.

All \w the|strong="H1696"\w* foolish \w of|strong="H7161"\w* heart \w were|strong="H7161"\w* troubled. \w They|strong="H1696"\w* \w have|strong="H1696"\w* slept their sleep; \w and|strong="H1696"\w* all \w the|strong="H1696"\w* men \w of|strong="H7161"\w* riches \w have|strong="H1696"\w* found \w nothing|strong="H0408"\w* \w in|strong="H1696"\w* their hands.

\w At|strong="H3808"\w* thy rebuke, O \w God|strong="H3808"\w* \w of|strong="H4161"\w* Jacob, \w they|strong="H3588"\w* \w have|strong="H3588"\w* all slumbered \w that|strong="H3588"\w* mounted \w on|strong="H3808"\w* horseback.
Thou art terrible, \w and|strong="H0430"\w* \w who|strong="H0430"\w* \w shall|strong="H2088"\w* resist thee? \w from|strong="H0430"\w* \w that|strong="H3588"\w* time thy wrath.

Thou hast caused \w judgment|strong="H3027"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w be|strong="H3027"\w* \w heard|strong="H3588"\w* \w from|strong="H3027"\w* heaven: \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w earth|strong="H0776"\w* trembled \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w was|strong="H3068"\w* still,

\w When|strong="H3290"\w* \w God|strong="H0430"\w* arose \w in|strong="H0430"\w* judgment, \w to|strong="H0430"\w* save \w all|strong="H5769"\w* \w the|strong="H0589"\w* meek \w of|strong="H0430"\w* \w the|strong="H0589"\w* earth.

\w For|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* thought \w of|strong="H3605"\w* \w man|strong="H7563"\w* \w shall|strong="H7563"\w* give \w praise|strong="H7311"\w* \w to|strong="H3605"\w* thee: \w and|strong="H6662"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* remainders \w of|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* thought \w shall|strong="H7563"\w* keep holiday \w to|strong="H3605"\w* thee.
Vow ye, and pay to the Lord your God: all you that are round about him bring presents. To him that is terrible,
Even to him who taketh away the spirit of princes: to the terrible with the kings of the earth.
